<===> cycle.json
{"g": "first", "h": "second"}

<===> cycle.liquid
== Bare cycle (anonymous group via args) ==
{% cycle "a", "b", "c" %}{% cycle "a", "b", "c" %}{% cycle "a", "b", "c" %}{% cycle "a", "b", "c" %}

== Literal-named groups have independent state ==
{% cycle "x": 1, 2 %}{% cycle "y": 1, 2 %}{% cycle "x": 1, 2 %}{% cycle "y": 1, 2 %}

== Variable group: same variable cycles together ==
{% cycle g: 1, 2, 3 %}{% cycle g: 1, 2, 3 %}{% cycle g: 1, 2, 3 %}{% cycle g: 1, 2, 3 %}

== Different variables resolving to different keys keep state separate ==
{% cycle g: 1, 2 %}{% cycle h: 1, 2 %}{% cycle g: 1, 2 %}{% cycle h: 1, 2 %}
